A hospital maintains a database of doctors and patient appointments.
Each doctor can handle only a limited number of patients per day.

The hospital wants to automate appointment booking using a Stored Procedure.
When a patient requests an appointment, the system must:

Check whether the doctor still has available slots.

If slots are available → book the appointment.
If slots are full → show a message "Doctor not available today".

Create a Stored Procedure to perform this operation automatically.

